  "text": "We estimated all-cause mortality following therapy initiation by race/ethnicity, and sex, standardized to the total cohort at therapy initiation to control for baseline differences in health status. We view race, ethnicity, and sex as markers for unmeasured factors, such as environment, income, social status, social capital, discrimination, structural violence and other phenomena, which may partially or completely explain the demographic disparities we observed [CITATION_1] . We did not standardize for these factors because our purpose was not to explain demographic disparities but rather to document their presence and estimate their magnitude.",
